td-50915d: Serialize checkpoint creation with account lock
Status: [in_progress]
Type: bug | Priority: P1
Labels: review-finding, code-quality

Description:
create_checkpoint/1 reads latest_log then inserts without transaction/advisory lock (app/lib/app/audit.ex:86, app/lib/app/audit.ex:162), so concurrent create_log_entry/2 can produce checkpoints that are no longer at chain head by commit time. Suggested fix: wrap create_checkpoint/1 in Repo.transaction with same per-account lock strategy used by create_log_entry/2 before reading latest_log and inserting. Found by: Code Quality, Fresh Eyes.

Acceptance Criteria:
Concurrent log writes during create_checkpoint/1 cannot produce stale checkpoints; add a deterministic concurrency test showing checkpoint.sequence_number equals current account head after operation.

