td-31343a: Handle checksum payload delimiter errors without raising
Status: [in_progress]
Type: bug | Priority: P2
Labels: review-finding, security

Description:
create_log_entry/2 computes checksum before insert and does not catch Chain errors (app/lib/app/audit.ex:29); Chain rejects payload fields containing '|' by raising ArgumentError (app/lib/app/audit/chain.ex:135). This can crash request paths instead of returning an error tuple when user-controlled values include delimiter characters. Suggested fix: validate/sanitize delimiter-sensitive fields before checksum computation or rescue and convert failures into {:error, changeset}-style responses. Found by: Security, Code Quality.

Acceptance Criteria:
Calling create_log_entry/2 with delimiter-bearing string input returns a structured error (no exception escape), and a regression test proves process stability.

