td-d189ce: Harden advisory lock key to reduce cross-account collisions
Status: [in_progress]
Type: chore | Priority: P3
Labels: review-finding, performance

Description:
lock_account/1 uses :erlang.phash2(account_id) with default range (app/lib/app/audit.ex:118), which can collide across tenants and serialize unrelated account writes. This weakens the intended cross-account concurrency guarantee under larger tenant counts. Suggested fix: move to a wider deterministic lock key strategy (e.g., two-int advisory lock keys from UUID components or explicit larger hash space) and document collision behavior. Found by: Code Quality, Fresh Eyes.

Acceptance Criteria:
Advisory lock key generation uses a collision-resistant strategy with tests/docs demonstrating independent locking for distinct account IDs.

